    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1592"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1592">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.5212/32.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: In the note which I addressed
                    to you on February 6 last, on the subject of the attempt to arrest Sr. Angel del
                    Caso by order of General Carranza, I stated inadvertently that Sr. del Caso was
                    the Confidential Agent of the Spanish Government to <pb facs="1171" n="1055"
                        xml:id="pg_1055"/> General Villa; but I have subsequently been informed by
                    my colleague the Spanish Minister to Mexico, that Sr. del Caso’s appointment of
                    Confidential Agent of the Spanish Government was to the President elected by the
                    Convention of Aguascalientes.</p>
                <p>Please take note of this information and believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
